definition.value: A 2-oxo monocarboxylic acid anion resulting from the removal of the proton from the carboxy group of 2-oxooctadecanoic acid (stearic acid). The major species at pH 7.3.
A tetrasaccharide consisting of sucrose having an alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-alpha-D-galactosyl moiety attached at the 6-position of the glucose.
A 1,3-thiazolemonocarboxylic acid consisting of 3,5-dihydrothiophene-4-carboxylic acid having a 6-hydroxybenzothiazol-2-yl group at the 2-position.

A non-proteinogenic alpha-amino acid that is arginine carrying a methyl group at position 3. It is a rare amino acid produced by Pseudomonas syringae syringae, with a strong toxicity against Pseudomonas syringae glycinea, two soybean pathogens.
